Timoshenko was sentenced to seven years in prison in October for concluding an allegedly detrimental contract with Russia on the purchase of natural gas.
The ruling has not yet come to an end, and the appeal of the convicted will be brought to court in December.
Timoshenko himself describes the verdict as political revenge of the regime and also in the West, the trial raised the suspicion of the bias of the court.
The request, paragraph 365, on the basis of which the Prime Minister was sentenced to be removed from the Criminal Code, was supported by 147 MPs.
226 votes would have been required for its adoption.
