The menu of a fat-addicted child: he does not have breakfast and eats sausage for dinner
More than a third of children aged 9 to 13 have problems with obesity, with 9 percent of all students and 5 percent of all children being overweight.
Recent surveys have proven - obese children mostly come from families with an unhealthy lifestyle.
This shows once again how important for a person’s healthy development is the environment in which he grows up and the examples that surround him are.
On the tables of obese children, sausages are up to half more often on the table than in families where normal-weight children live.
More than 19 percent of overweight children had fries for dinner on the day before the reconnaissance campaign under the motto "Obesity is no coincidence".
In families with thickets, sports is not exactly a favorite activity, but the majority of today's students are also concerned - only 15 percent answered that their parents find time for active exercise at least once a week.
Survey of 900 children
The survey took place at the end of the school year last year, with nearly 900 children from primary schools surveyed throughout the Czech Republic.
This was already the second year of the "Obesity is not a coincidence" campaign, which is supported by the General Health Insurance and the Unilever Society.
So far, more than 12,000 students from 4th and 8th grades have participated in the project.
Unhealthy diet and lack of exercise in the family are crucial factors that are responsible for the frighteningly increasing number of children with overweight or even obesity.
“Only half of the children surveyed reported eating breakfast-breakfast-lunch-second evening-breakfast five times a day – one of the main prerequisites for a healthy diet,” says one of the survey results.
No breakfast and sausage for dinner
Experts point out that even relative little things, such as the regular breakfast time of the family, are important for the healthy development of a child.
In the Czech Republic, however, only 23 percent of the families of the students have breakfast.
And - in most families, everyone eats breakfast on their own.
The worst was the finding that in every tenth family there is no breakfast at all.
Breakfast is considered the cornerstone of a healthy daily diet.
Among other things, the survey test showed that in the families of overweight children, unhealthy fries are consumed much more often.
And almost everyone – regardless of weight – drinks sweet sodas every day (70 percent)
While more than 40 percent of the children surveyed do sports, only less than half of their parents do — only 15 percent.
Create your own menu
Another part of the survey allowed selected children (204 boys and 172 girls from 13 schools) to compile their own meal plans based on the possibilities offered by appetite and opinion.
“What Czech children between the ages of 12 and 15 prefer in terms of nutrition is far from the ideal of a healthy diet.
Among her favorite dishes were many meals, meat dishes and, of course, sweets.
"Alarming above all is the great popularity of sweet lemonades," the final report on this survey emphasizes.
At lunch, i.e. the main dish, pasta beat just in front of poultry.
The children almost did not like legumes and the popularity of fish and vegetable dishes as lunches was very low.
Return to Health
At the same time, the survey also showed that the children are quite willing to change their eating habits when they get correct information.
"In many cases, the control group of respondents who completed the questionnaire after the conclusion of the informative lecture "Obesity is not accidental", there was a significant shift in preferences towards principles of healthy eating," the results of the project are cited.
This was noticeable, for example, with the sweet limos, where many children began to give priority to ordinary water.
The children also crossed in the questionnaire much more often poultry or fish as the main course of the day and were willing to eat less dumplings or sweet foods.
Professionals claim - a stylist must also be a good psychologist
In the introductory article about how stylists learn, I had a bit of a fuss that that was a little too much stuff for the start.
I didn’t know at all what was to come.
Lectures by three professionals from the industry, the clothing of problematic figures and a seminar on how the "on the pitch" runs.
It's supposed to get worse.
The closer the exam comes, the more information and practical tasks we have before us.
But even if the course takes place every Saturday and Sunday, it is still full.
This time, we discussed with Director Alena (no one man takes part in the course) how to dress a woman who has no ideally proportioned figure.
And that is, after all, most of us.
Some have a neck too short, others a figure too young without decent curves and again others are molly.
It is up to the stylist to visually hide wide shoulders, to lengthen the neck or to highlight the necessary curves.
We also got tips on how to attract a woman like Jennifer Lopez -- that is, with a big bust, a wide hip and a narrow waist -- pretty and figurative without her looking too provocative.
For example, if the difference between waist and hips is so great that the skirt or pants really don't fit, you should at least have a piece tailored.
You will certainly not regret this, because well-fitting clothes are simply priceless.
In such a bespoke skirt you feel much better than in one of the rod that always slips up and down, protrudes in the waist, etc.
Young figures can, in turn, allow themselves to wear clothing with folds, studs, applications, embroidery or raffing.
With this amount of information and types of figures, I am glad that I have a whole week of time to let everything go through my mind thoroughly.
And yet I’m afraid that it’s almost impossible in the face of homework assignments.
Each of the students was assigned a celebrity, for which she should design suitable outfits - daywear and evening dress.
We should take into account the current appearance, the fashion style of the corresponding star and his type of figure.
I'm supposed to "dress up" Miranda Kerr, which you may know from the Victoria's Secret campaign.
Inside I rejoice, because this is much better for me personally than, for example, Britney Spears or Christina Aguilera, who has probably gained a hundred pounds lately (well, that's a little exaggerated), or even the young Selena Gomez.
We should cut out the garments from magazines or search, print and then graphically edit them on the Internet.
In the "Moodboard", as the whole result is called, our very personal style and our relationship to graphic design should then be expressed.
It is very important to also think about the graphic side of the styling.
The stylist not only attracts the models purely physically, but also designs the so-called product page in the journals (according to specific specifications, for example, trend handbags, coats, etc.).
The stylist and designer Mario Kameník told us about this.
But only on Sunday.
This means that a stylist must have a good overall overview.
The Saturday lecture, filled with information about types of figures, was seasoned by three visitors from the industry:
by stylist Jan Pokorný, fashion designer Jakub Polanka and fashion photographer Ben Ren<0xC4><0x8D>.
Jakub reminded us that fashion is illusion and that a stylist should be able to take advantage of it.
And a smart stylist is able to work with a single garment in very different ways.
The magic word is variability.
For example, you can wear a trench coat as usual over the jeans, like a t-shirt or coat, but you can also wear it on the naked body, put on heels and wear it as a dress.
It is enough to pull up the sleeves or the collar and the whole look looks very different.
“Play with it,” he stressed.
But most of all, the following advice came to me: "First you have to know the rules perfectly."
“Then you can hurt her,” Jakub said.
I finally realize why we need to punch all these teachings, what to combine with what and why, even if you often get to see quite different things in fashion journals.
Not to mention fashion shows.
Thanks to photographer Ben, I now know that a stylist must have prepared a lot more clothing variations than he ultimately photographs.
So you have to be prepared for a fashion story with ten pages (i.e. ten outfits) to style at least fifteen.
And also that the clothing on the photo in combination with other accessories sometimes looks quite different than in reality.
So you have to count on all of this when designing the outfit.
The fact that image and style sometimes make up half of the success was also confirmed by Jan Pokorný.
You just have to look at Madonna, a not exactly brilliant singer who made image and marketing a world star.
In the Czech Republic, one is more reserved to the services of a stylist.
Also well-known personalities often consider this to be thrown away money (the main thing is that I bring something as I look is secondary).
And if someone of us can be styled, then we should expect that he or she is very likely to impose on us a completely different (smaller) size than he or she actually needs.
Then you only need to google to determine with certainty that the tabloid is writing, the corresponding celebrity has increased or decreased, etc.
Jan and Mario urged us on Sunday not to believe that a stylist just needs to focus on fashion and then "assemble" the outfit.
In his work, he must communicate above all with the people he styles and he must be a wise psychologist.
Appreciate people without being obsessed and standing by their opinion.
“If any manager orders us to look at her wardrobe and add up to pretty pieces, then we can’t clean out the entire wardrobe and say, ‘Oh my God, that’s terrible.’”
"You have to find at least a few commendable things to recommend what you can wear," Mario says.
He also showed us quite concretely what a so-called "place bag" must contain.
So this is a bag that you button at the waist and in which you carry all the necessary properties.
Apart from clear things such as scissors, hair removal scrubbers or safety needles, it also contains such utensils as a nylon thread (which helps the stylist to photograph products such as handbags or hats), special clips, with which the clothes are sewn back, if it is not too large (plugging needles or other clamps).
But so that we can not only listen, but also try something practical, we learned how to properly glue shoes.
Even when photographing in the studio, where the floor is flat, you can damage the shoe sole, let alone the outside.
We glued and glued...
With the scissors you must not even touch the shoes, so that you do not damage them.
So you really have to go cleverly.
Mario pleased me by praising my "creation" without restrictions.
The aforementioned skill is not exactly my strength.
All of this was only a fraction of what we heard on the second weekend continuation course.
One thing has now become clear to me - devoting myself to styling at a professional level is not a breeze.
V Need for Speed: "The Run" - the illegal race across America
Rezension
The original carefree journey is made possible by a series of completely avoidable dilettant errors for the routine journey to the early shift.
Although it managed to fulfill the ambitions for a large part, what good is it if obviously no one wanted to do a little more.
Even before it came to the counters, the new part with the subtitle "The Run" aroused high expectations.
He promised to move the already aged game series "Need for Speed" once again to a new dimension and in the playable demonstration examples it did not seem to be just one of many action racing games.
We were also curious about how the adapted passages fall out, in which the main protagonist gets out of the car and continues on foot.
But as you’re used to with NFS, in the end, a lot is different than you expected.
Sure - potentially it is quite decent arcade races, but overall the game is diminished by some superfluous mistakes that have been present in this series for more or less a few years.
So they are actually no longer mistakes, but rather signs of an in principle incomprehensible laziness of the game developers.
The adventure starts very well.
The first time you are introduced to history, whose main character Jack has certain personal problems; the only solution seems to be to participate in an illegal race across America.
In San Francisco, on the west coast, you sit at the steering wheel - with the task of being the first in New York.
The basic idea contains a whole host of interesting elements.
The entire route is divided into ten stages and more than fifty individual races.
This means that each race is run on a different track and that the individual stages take place in a different, sufficiently different and interesting environment.
It doesn’t feel like the game will always offer the same thing.
Some environments are still very pretty to look at, although the technical level of the graphics does not exceed that of the previous parts of the series.
So nothing world-moving.
But the ride through the desert, through autumnal landscape or high up through deep snowy landscape looks visually very pleasant.
Occasionally, atypical elements bring a little variety to the individual races.
In the desert, for example, you are surprised by a desert storm that greatly restricts the view.
In the mountains, in turn, you have to be hellishly careful not to be spilled by an avalanche.
By the way, the individual races are built quite well in succession.
Only a few, but they are enough.
For a while you try to overtake the prescribed number of opponents (in principle a classic race), then you have time to catch up (classic race against the stopwatch), then you expect a further personal duel with a single opponent.
And the police are also involved, who want to mess up the whole thing.
A novelty are passages in which Jack leaves the car.
This is more about certain interactive animations, in which Jack runs away from anyone and where the player has to help him by pressing the right button at the right moment.
So nothing complicated.
Surprisingly, however, there are far fewer such passages in the game than you would expect (in particular, probably only three).
Ultimately, this is more to the advantage of the thing, because this element at least has no chance of getting bored - it belongs in the context of the above mentioned one of the elements that make the game more varied.
The driving model follows in the footsteps of the previous parts.
That is, from today’s point of view, although it does not tear up trees, on the other hand you could not claim it to be bad.
If you are looking for realistic simulations, you have to look elsewhere.
But an action-packed race will continue to do quite well with the local driving model, although you could find better in the competition.
Until then, everything is in order.
Real problems only appear after a certain period of time.
Unlike the driving model, the collision model is not entirely OK.
A game of this type is hardly expected to calculate complicated deformations and collisions, but if you have virtually no idea how the car is behaving before any impact on any object, obviously not everything is okay.
Typical example: When you narrowly overtake or pass by oncoming cars, you "scramble" the other car in some places only easily, but in other, almost identical situations, you get into the loop and turn wild pirouettes.
Or drive the cart to scrap.
Thanks to the restart system, this does not matter any more, it is always annoying.
The restarts are solved like this: if you have total damage or land far off the track, then you throw the game back to the last point of the track.
Only - in each race you have only five restarts.
When you've exhausted them, everything starts from the beginning.
So the restarts are more like a tool, in case something does not succeed, but you should not rely on it.
Sometimes, however, even the restart does not help, it does not help anything but to learn the critical section from the head.
It is very unpleasant that the same things often happen in the same places.
Some curves, for example, you have to go through in a very specific way, otherwise you just don't pass through.
Elsewhere you will always meet "civil" cars in the same configuration at the appropriate location, whether you are the first or fifth, five seconds earlier or a minute later.
This is particularly annoying in situations when you see that the opponent passes two coming cars in front of a game, but until you get there yourself, the cars are already in such a position that you have to bypass them or brake them.
And it doesn’t matter when you get there, because everything is designed in such a way that this situation always comes close to your nose.
The counterparts have other advantages.
Throughout the game there are a few places where you are always overtaken in the same place by the same opponent and again here regardless of the timing.
The most insane is this at the end of the game on the long bridge that you pass in the opposite direction.
The opponent must obviously overtake one here on hell get out.
And if he’s in front of you, of course, he’s taking the view away, so you’ll start driving your own car a few times in Klump.
Of course - you just want to make the game more exciting and exciting but this intention is so clear that it quickly misses you the pleasure of the game.
And that’s a pity, because despite the simpler driving model, the game is overall quite entertaining and sometimes so action-packed that you almost don’t know where your head is.
And in principle, it doesn't matter what's "to blame" for it - the concept with fifty unique routes, the arrangement of the races in a way that no boredom can arise, or something quite different...
An unusual idea is also the change of car during the races.
You should not overlook the gas stations on the route, because here you can change the car, although in most cases the car that you currently have is sufficient.
The cars are divided into three categories.
The sports cars are well suited for urban areas, the strong American limousines for the straight highways and exotic super sports cars for the technical rides, for example on the serpentines in the mountains.
Hand in hand with the game’s story mode also goes the task mode (challenges) – that is, the races in the individual locations that you know from history.
There are not only medals, but also experience points for your own profile, which is common for the tasks (challenges) and the story.
In order to get to the higher driver level, different items need to be opened up: from the car to the backgrounds for the profile.
This is at the same time connected to the online Autolog function, which compares your own results with those of other players and also provides for further collective functions.
One of the other incomprehensible carvers is a situation in the last race in history.
Here you get by car into a subway tunnel (my way), where you race long on the rails (my way) in the dark.
On the tacho, numbers look between 150 and 200 km/h (my way), but there suddenly comes a subway from behind and drives an uncompromising one to scrap.
In our editorial we will probably argue for a long time whether this was a blackout of the game designers or whether the authors think we are so stupid.
The technical side is nothing overwhelming but at least the overall visual impression is quite appealing in most cases and even brilliant here and there.
It is all the more annoying that at some exciting moments the refresh rate slows down and this is sometimes quite dramatic.
However, this applies in particular to accidents with a larger number of participants, where a continuous FPS does not benefit you anyway.
The sound reproduction is OK and the soundtrack is a matter of taste.
In an effort to appeal to as broad a scale as possible rather young audiences, a soundtrack a lá "from everyone something" was created - but who buys such a game already because of the music?!
The overall impression of Need for Speed: The Run? The feelings are rather mixed.
If the game weren’t curtailed by the aforementioned totally unnecessary mistakes, we would have been able to contend with the chest tone of conviction that The Run is the best piece of NFS in recent years.
But that's how the game looks somehow unfinished.
In itself a classy pleasure, but you should be prepared to get these mistakes in your eyes with the power of airport headlights.
