This was the work of the doctor who identified the body of Alfonso Cano.
A lophoscopist from Cali went into history as the man who identified "Alfonso Cano".
The work of these officials plays a key role.
Last November 4th, a lophoscopist from the Cali Prosecutor’s Investigation Unit (CTI) came in as the man who confirmed the identity of the leader of the FARC (Fuerzas Armadas Revolucionarias de Colombia - Revolutionary Armed Forces of Colombia), “Alfonso Cano” by comparing fingerprints.
Of the seven lophoscopists in the CTI department, this week Eliazar González had been on standby, a man from Puerto Tejada who has been involved in criminal investigations for 21 years.
At the beginning of his career, González worked in communities of Chocó, where he often had to go to the jungle for five days to reach the place where the bodies were to be identified.
In 2000 he settled in Valle above and after completing the required courses he specialized in lophoscopy, which is the examination of the skin exposed to friction, i.e. the hand and foot surfaces.
In the week of action against the so-called Alfonso Cano, Eliazar was told to pack clothes for at least three days.
Something great awaited him.
Friday night he flew in a helicopter from Palmira to Cauca.
He knew that he was to identify two bodies, and that there was suspicion that one could be that of the man who had led the oldest guerrilla in the world, so he was to take the ten-finger print sheet by Guillermo León Sáenz (his real name).
However, when he reached the place where the body was most investigated, he could not identify it because of its physical appearance, for it was not in the least similar to the images he had seen in the mass media.
He had no beard, was dressed like a local farmer, didn’t wear glasses, and was much thinner.
But fingerprints don't lie.
Armed with a magnifying glass, ink, a planting cell and a flashlight, Eliazar compared the fingerprints of the body to those on the print sheet.
He had seen it right: it was Alfonso Cano.
That same night, this man from Puerto Tejada was responsible for telling the Minister of Defense, Juan Carlos Pinzón, that he was in fact the head of the FARC.
On track search
The appreciation given by President Juan Manuel Santos Eliazar González at a press conference on the use against "Cano" was very important for a dactyloscope from Sijín in Cali.
Many people do not know our work.
Dactyloscopy is an exact science with no error rate, which can be a key factor in the resolution of a crime.
Lophoscopists not only identify bodies, they also support investigations into murder and robbery and confirm the identity of the arrested persons.
When they are arrested, many criminals present false identification documents or they have none.
We take their fingerprints and find them in the database.
The researcher told us that in the event of a theft, he had to tear a piece of a wall out of a house, because the thief had leaned with his hand exactly at this point when he pulled out a safe full of jewelry and money.
“Walls are difficult because their surfaces are unsuitable for taking fingerprints, but in this case we were able to take the entire handprint and identify the offender who participated in multiple thefts,” he recalled.
With the help of fingerprints, murder suspects can also be relieved or charged.
Recently, a dead man was found surrounded by bottles of liquor.
The investigation suspected a family member to be suspicious, and in fact a fingerprint on the bottle matched.
Although this does not guarantee that it is the murderer, he is linked to the place where the crime was committed.
A CTI dactyloscopist explained that “the fingerprints would be taken from the object with chemical or physical reagents.”
When they appear, a plant cellar or ribbon is used to carry.
After that, the prints are sent to the Asif, which is the criminal database, or to the Personal Status Office.
"The problem is that there are still many Colombians without ID papers," said the expert from the CTI.
He said not everything was as it would be depicted in the TV series SCI.
Just as not all gold is what shines, not all you touch is a fingerprint.
But it can still be used if you make a corresponding comparison.
